      • save

        public void save(T... entities)
          throws org.springframework.dao.DataAccessException
        Description copied from interface: GenericDAO

        For each entity, if the id of the entity is null or zero, add it to the datastore and assign it an id; otherwise, update the corresponding entity in the datastore with the properties of this entity. In either case the entity passed to this method will be attached to the session.

        If an entity to update is already attached to the session, this method will have no effect. If an entity to update has the same id as another instance already attached to the session, an error will be thrown.

        Specified by:
        save in interface GenericDAO<T,ID extends Serializable>
        Throws:
        org.springframework.dao.DataAccessException

      • update

        public void update(T... entities)
            throws org.springframework.dao.DataAccessException
        Description copied from interface: GenericDAO
        Update the persistent instances with the identifier of the given detached instance. If there is a persistent instance with the same identifier, an exception is thrown. This operation cascades to associated instances if the association is mapped with cascade="save-update".
        Specified by:
        update in interface GenericDAO<T,ID extends Serializable>
